  "text": "and of the TSPO ligand 2 (Figure 9 ). After 24 h treatment with the test compounds, cells exhibited only a slight modification of the cell cycle distribution. As expected, oxaliplatin delayed the S-phase and started to accumulate cells in G2/M-phase and G0/G1 phase [48] . Compounds 3 and 1 induced no notable changes compared to oxaliplatin. The TSPO ligand 2 induced a sub-G0/G1 cell population after 24 h, consistent with the formation of apoptotic cells as previously demonstrated for this class of compounds [CITATION_1] . ",
